23
00:01:11,840 --> 00:01:12,840
Midnight kidnapping

24
00:01:57,840 --> 00:01:58,840
Hello? (Answering the phone here)

25
00:01:58,840 --> 00:02:00,840
Ah, what?!

26
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:17,840
Ring-a-ling~

27
00:02:20,840 --> 00:02:21,840
What's that sound?

28
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:22,840
What's going on?

29
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:23,840
Time to get up!

30
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:25,840
Why are you in my house so early?

31
00:02:25,840 --> 00:02:27,680
What was all that noise just now?

32
00:02:27,680 --> 00:02:29,719
Huh? What's this?

33
00:02:29,719 --> 00:02:33,300
Hehe~ This is a gift for Locky!

34
00:02:33,300 --> 00:02:36,439
It's called the Super Power Combo Alarm Clock!

35
00:02:36,439 --> 00:02:40,360
With this, Locky will never be late again!

36
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:41,280
And in return...

37
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:44,180
You have to treat Jingjing to three glasses of juice!

38
00:02:44,180 --> 00:02:46,659
Three glasses, three glasses!

39
00:02:46,659 --> 00:02:49,439
You wake me up and still want a gift?

40
00:02:49,439 --> 00:02:53,759
Hmph, so stingy!

41
00:02:55,840 --> 00:02:58,979
Oh, Jingjing...

42
00:02:58,979 --> 00:03:01,379
Where's Uncle?

43
00:03:01,379 --> 00:03:05,640
Uncle left you a note.

44
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:08,980
"Locky, I'm off on a small case.

45
00:03:08,980 --> 00:03:11,719
Rest well at home."

46
00:03:11,719 --> 00:03:15,699
Uncle's working a case and didn't take me along?

47
00:03:15,699 --> 00:03:19,020
Locky, come play with me!

48
00:03:19,020 --> 00:03:20,219
You big curly-head!

49
00:03:20,219 --> 00:03:22,060
I'm going to find Uncle!

50
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:37,560
So that's the gist of the case.

51
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:39,460
Detective Chen,

52
00:03:39,460 --> 00:03:41,759
do you have any thoughts?

53
00:03:41,759 --> 00:03:44,539
It does sound pretty strange.

54
00:03:44,539 --> 00:03:45,259
Uncle!!

55
00:03:45,259 --> 00:03:51,360
Oh wow, I never expected

56
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:52,879
you guys to find your way here yourselves.

57
00:03:52,879 --> 00:03:55,319
Locky,

58
00:03:55,319 --> 00:03:57,120
this was supposed to be a small case,

59
00:03:57,120 --> 00:03:59,659
so I didn't want to bother a big detective like you.

60
00:03:59,659 --> 00:04:01,560
No, no, no—

61
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:03,500
for a responsible detective,

62
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:06,099
there's no such thing as a big or small case.

63
00:04:06,099 --> 00:04:07,180
Excuse me.

64
00:04:07,180 --> 00:04:08,900
Who?

65
00:04:10,900 --> 00:04:13,560
You again, you ghost-like guy.

66
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:16,079
Why are you always following me?

67
00:04:16,079 --> 00:04:17,500
Sorry,

68
00:04:17,500 --> 00:04:19,519
but I have no interest

69
00:04:19,519 --> 00:04:20,459
in a kid who calls himself a detective.

70
00:04:20,459 --> 00:04:22,219
What—

71
00:04:22,219 --> 00:04:24,219
a k-kid?!

72
00:04:25,319 --> 00:04:29,079
I'm Detective Hawxing, here to assist with the case.

73
00:04:29,079 --> 00:04:32,439
Please, tell me without any embellishment

74
00:04:32,439 --> 00:04:34,199
the full details of the incident.

75
00:04:34,199 --> 00:04:38,519
Mr. Niake.

76
00:04:38,519 --> 00:04:39,480
They are

77
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:41,659
the most outstanding young detectives in this city.

78
00:04:41,659 --> 00:04:43,100
Don't let their age fool you—

79
00:04:43,100 --> 00:04:44,680
they have a real knack for cracking cases.

80
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:46,519
Sometimes they're even better than us adults.

81
00:04:46,519 --> 00:04:50,399
Hello there.

82
00:04:50,399 --> 00:04:53,500
Then let me go over the incident.

83
00:04:53,500 --> 00:04:55,480
Last night, when Mr. Nyack returned home,

84
00:04:55,480 --> 00:04:58,399
he saw an ambulance rescuing his mother, Ms. Taylor.

85
00:04:58,399 --> 00:05:00,180
That's how Mr. Nyack learned

86
00:05:00,180 --> 00:05:02,079
that his mother's pet dog had been kidnapped.

87
00:05:02,079 --> 00:05:04,579
His mother fainted from the shock.

88
00:05:04,579 --> 00:05:07,100
Then Mr. Nyack called the police.

89
00:05:07,100 --> 00:05:10,199
Since the pet dog wasn't a rare breed,

90
00:05:10,199 --> 00:05:13,500
Mr. Nyack found it strange that someone would kidnap it.

91
00:05:13,500 --> 00:05:17,980
So the suspect left no clues at all?

92
00:05:17,980 --> 00:05:19,620
There is a clue.

93
00:05:19,620 --> 00:05:21,120
The entire kidnapping

94
00:05:21,120 --> 00:05:23,259
was recorded in detail by surveillance cameras.

95
00:05:27,259 --> 00:05:28,579
Here it comes.

96
00:05:28,579 --> 00:05:43,259
Go, go, go!

97
00:05:43,259 --> 00:05:45,480
Go, go, go!

98
00:05:53,259 --> 00:06:08,779
So he's Santa Claus.

99
00:06:17,300 --> 00:06:19,699
That's the crime footage.

100
00:06:19,699 --> 00:06:23,039
Where was the kidnapper's last call made to?

101
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:26,819
The last call was made to the emergency center.

102
00:06:26,819 --> 00:06:31,760
I know who the criminal is.

103
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:34,240
Then who is it?

104
00:06:34,240 --> 00:06:35,580
That fast, huh?

105
00:06:35,580 --> 00:06:39,020
The suspect is Niak.

106
00:06:43,580 --> 00:06:44,020
La la la~

107
00:06:46,020 --> 00:06:47,259
First, it's this late at night,

108
00:06:47,259 --> 00:06:49,800
but the old lady opened the door without any hesitation.

109
00:06:49,960 --> 00:06:52,740
That means the person she saw must be someone she knows.

110
00:06:52,740 --> 00:06:57,660
Second, dogs usually bark and bite at strangers,

111
00:06:57,660 --> 00:07:00,079
but this one didn't.

112
00:07:00,079 --> 00:07:02,900
Clearly, he's very familiar with the criminal.

113
00:07:02,900 --> 00:07:05,819
Finally, the criminal even called an ambulance.

114
00:07:05,819 --> 00:07:08,100
That shows he really cares about the old lady's safety.

115
00:07:08,100 --> 00:07:13,379
All of this points to only one person: Mr. Niak is the criminal.

116
00:07:13,379 --> 00:07:17,519
No, no, it's not me. How could it be?

117
00:07:17,519 --> 00:07:20,780
No, it's not me, really not me. How could it be?

118
00:07:20,780 --> 00:07:22,680
Your judgment is too hasty.

119
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:28,860
Let me ask you: what's his motive? What reason does he have to steal his own mother's pet dog?

120
00:07:28,830 --> 00:07:29,000
What reason does he have to steal his own mother's pet dog?

121
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:32,000
Then you tell me, why didn't the dog bark?

122
00:07:32,660 --> 00:07:33,259
We're also puzzled about the dog's behavior.

123
00:07:33,660 --> 00:07:34,259
Pomeranians are usually easy to tease,

124
00:07:34,660 --> 00:07:35,259
and they're known for barking a lot.

125
00:07:35,660 --> 00:07:37,259
But Mr. Niak said the Pomeranian he found was very special.

126
00:07:37,660 --> 00:07:38,259
Gentle and doesn't bark.

127
00:07:44,660 --> 00:07:45,259
So she gave it to her own mother.

128
00:07:46,259 --> 00:07:48,519
So according to what Locky just said

129
00:07:48,519 --> 00:07:50,899
Snatching away the dog I gave to my own mother.

130
00:07:50,899 --> 00:07:52,759
That doesn't hold up at all.

131
00:07:52,759 --> 00:07:57,000
Why did the old lady open the door so easily, then?

132
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:59,399
That night,

133
00:07:59,399 --> 00:08:01,800
Mr. Nyack is supposed to be here at 9:30.

134
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:03,000
Visiting my mother.

135
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:04,439
So, Ms. Taylor...

136
00:08:04,439 --> 00:08:06,399
Thought he was his own son, so he let his guard down.

137
00:08:06,399 --> 00:08:07,899
For the ambulance part—

138
00:08:07,899 --> 00:08:10,219
Guess this suspect still has some sympathy after all.

139
00:08:10,219 --> 00:08:11,800
Special dog.

140
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:13,279
Some are special.

141
00:08:13,279 --> 00:08:14,139
Where have you been?

142
00:08:14,279 --> 00:08:15,139
Peeing

143
00:08:15,139 --> 00:08:17,379
Drinking that much juice again.

144
00:08:17,379 --> 00:08:18,399
I'm not bringing you along on cases anymore.

145
00:08:18,399 --> 00:08:19,399
La la la la

146
00:08:19,399 --> 00:08:21,539
What've you got in your hand?

147
00:08:21,539 --> 00:08:24,099
This? Jingjing just found it.

148
00:08:24,099 --> 00:08:26,139
Seems like it's about a cute little dog.

149
00:08:30,139 --> 00:08:33,139
No more juice on the job, or you're off the case?

150
00:08:41,139 --> 00:08:42,799
Ms. Taylor, hello.

151
00:08:42,799 --> 00:08:44,879
The First National Beautiful Dog Contest

152
00:08:44,879 --> 00:08:46,679
Cordially invites you to bring your beloved dog

153
00:08:46,679 --> 00:08:47,959
To participate in the competition

154
00:08:50,959 --> 00:08:51,879
This might be a clue

155
00:08:51,879 --> 00:08:55,179
I... I'm really worried about my mother

156
00:08:55,179 --> 00:08:57,779
I need to go to the hospital to see her

157
00:08:57,779 --> 00:09:00,799
Yeah, I think we should head to the hospital too

158
00:09:00,799 --> 00:09:02,679
To check on Ms. Taylor's current condition

159
00:09:02,679 --> 00:09:04,240
And once she wakes up

160
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:05,519
We might be able to learn

161
00:09:05,519 --> 00:09:06,479
More clues

162
00:09:06,479 --> 00:09:08,379
How about we split into three teams?

163
00:09:08,379 --> 00:09:09,379
Officer Sima,

164
00:09:09,379 --> 00:09:11,379
Please accompany Mr. Niake to the hospital

165
00:09:11,379 --> 00:09:16,200
Me, Locky, and Jingjing will check out the contest registration spot

166
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:19,860
Hawxing will stay at Shuiyunli

167
00:09:19,860 --> 00:09:21,939
In case the criminal calls

168
00:09:21,939 --> 00:09:22,700
Sorry

169
00:09:22,700 --> 00:09:25,539
I still need to investigate other clues my own way

170
00:09:25,539 --> 00:09:28,740
Hmph, such a goody-two-shoes

171
00:09:28,740 --> 00:09:31,399
【ED】

172
00:09:31,399 --> 00:09:34,399
That way, once we get there, we can ask around

173
00:09:34,399 --> 00:09:38,360
Its name is Little Kitten

174
00:09:38,360 --> 00:09:38,759
Ah

175
00:10:08,360 --> 00:10:14,360
Look, tomorrow is waving to me from the horizon

176
00:10:14,360 --> 00:10:21,899
Every day from sunrise to sunset, spinning into time's fantasy of lights

177
00:10:21,899 --> 00:10:27,440
Waiting for each second, every moment of life

178
00:10:27,440 --> 00:10:37,080
Bright eyes are sparkling, reflecting sunny smiles

179
00:10:37,080 --> 00:10:42,400
He's at the bridge, at the silent crossroads